A yearly subscription is refundable within 14 days of purchase and includes a 365-day membership. “If all G-7 countries met their fair share target, this initiative would be two-thirds funded — and it would be 90% funded if all G-20 countries made their fair share contributions,” he said. The nations should also support the proposed Trade-Related Aspects of Intellectual Property Rights (TRIPS) waiver to address and engage in negotiations that would allow for the rapid and widespread production of medical products in Africa and across the world, he said. “The negotiations must be concluded soon because the cost of inaction is measured in people’s lives,” Ramaphosa said. “If the world is to emerge from this grave crisis, it is essential that we work together to mobilise and direct resources to those countries in the greatest need — and that we do so now.”